bug.short_desc: [abrt] mate-control-center: g_type_check_instance_cast(): mate-display-properties killed by SIGSEGV

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: Because the suspend in Mate doesn't work, I use a script to suspend my system at night: #!/bin/bash /usr/bin/dbus-send --system --print-reply --dest="org.freedesktop.login1" /org/freedesktop/login1 org.freedesktop.login1.Manager.Suspend boolean:true
Usually, it works fine. This morning, I hit the power button on my laptop to unsuspend it and one of my external monitors did not start. I went to System and then Displays. I tried hitting just the apply button since the monitors were all detected, but that didn't bring back the second external monitor. It was just a few seconds after this that the program crashed, but I'm not 100% sure on exactly where I clicked, if anywhere. It may have been to try unchecking one of the monitors or maybe hitting apply again.
Version-Release number of selected component: mate-control-center-1.12.1-2.fc24
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.6.3 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: mate-display-properties crash_function: g_type_check_instance_cast executable: /usr/bin/mate-display-properties global_pid: 1029 kernel: 4.5.0-0.rc0.git1.1.fc24.x86_64 runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (10 frames) #0 g_type_check_instance_cast at gtype.c:4065 #1 on_output_event at xrandr-capplet.c:1575 #2 emit_input at scrollarea.c:1016 #3 process_event at scrollarea.c:1066 #4 process_gdk_event at scrollarea.c:1103 #5 foo_scroll_area_motion at scrollarea.c:1134 #6 _gtk_marshal_BOOLEAN__BOXED at gtkmarshalers.c:86 #11 gtk_widget_event_internal at gtkwidget.c:5017 #12 gtk_widget_event at gtkwidget.c:4814 #13 gtk_propagate_event at gtkmain.c:2501

This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase
Hmm, that suspend does not work in f24 is new for me, but i do not install f24 on my notebook before beta release, so i can't reproduce it. Is the other issue reproducible?
Btw. on normal box i see no crash with mate-display-properties.
On my notebook works suspend very well. Is the issue still exists?
